<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1155,1756]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1336,1360]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, D. S." box="[326,503,1335,1359]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="95 - 118" refId="ref48564" refString="Johnson, D. S. (1958) The Indo-West Pacific species of the genus Polyonyx (Crustacea, Decapoda, Porcellanidae), Annals of Zoology, AGRA, 2 (8), 95 - 118." type="journal article" year="1958">Johnson (1958)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the records of 
<taxonomicName box="[868,1010,1336,1360]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvidens">
<emphasis box="[868,882,1337,1360]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[900,1010,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">parvidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1073,1219,1336,1360]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paucidens">
<emphasis box="[1073,1087,1337,1360]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1105,1219,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">paucidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[1268,1431,1335,1359]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="158 - 164" refId="ref51316" refString="Nobili, G. (1905 a) Decapodes nouveaux des cotes d'Arabie et du Golfe Persique (Diagnoses preliminaires). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 11, 158 - 164." type="journal article" year="1905">Nobili (1905a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[151,220,1372,1396]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="13 - 159" refId="ref51383" refString="Nobili, G. (1906 a) Crustaces decapodes et stomatopodes. In: Mission J. Bonnier et Ch. Perez (Golfe Persique, 1901). Bulletin Scientifique de la France et de la Belgique, 40, 13 - 159, pls. 2 - 7." type="journal article" year="1906">1906a</bibRefCitation>
) from the Persian Gulf were based on juvenile specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miers" authorityYear="1884" box="[918,1046,1372,1396]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesulus">
<emphasis box="[918,932,1373,1396]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[948,1046,1372,1396]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">obesulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[1061,1198,1372,1396]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="49 - 65" refId="ref47698" refString="Haig, J. (1966) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea, Anomura) of the Iranian Gulf and Gulf of Oman. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening i Kobenhaven, 129, 49 - 65." type="journal article" year="1966">Haig (1966)</bibRefCitation>
supported Johnson’s idea in synonymising Nobili’s species 
<taxonomicName box="[602,743,1408,1432]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvidens">
<emphasis box="[602,616,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[633,743,1408,1432]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">parvidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[806,950,1408,1432]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paucidens">
<emphasis box="[806,820,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[837,950,1408,1432]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">paucidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miers" authorityYear="1884" box="[1022,1152,1408,1432]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesulus">
<emphasis box="[1022,1036,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1054,1152,1408,1432]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">obesulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[1170,1310,1407,1431]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="49 - 65" refId="ref47698" refString="Haig, J. (1966) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea, Anomura) of the Iranian Gulf and Gulf of Oman. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening i Kobenhaven, 129, 49 - 65." type="journal article" year="1966">Haig (1966)</bibRefCitation>
noted that juvenile specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miers" authorityYear="1884" box="[412,542,1444,1468]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesulus">
<emphasis box="[412,426,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[444,542,1444,1468]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">obesulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble more closely the description of 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1178,1444,1468]" class="Malacostraca" family="Porcellanidae" genus="Polyonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvidens">
<emphasis box="[1036,1050,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1068,1178,1444,1468]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">parvidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[1227,1398,1444,1468]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="158 - 164" refId="ref51316" refString="Nobili, G. (1905 a) Decapodes nouveaux des cotes d'Arabie et du Golfe Persique (Diagnoses preliminaires). Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris, 11, 158 - 164." type="journal article" year="1905">Nobili (1905a)</bibRefCitation>
, in particular, regarding the presence of spines on the anterior margin of the merus and carpus of the cheliped. 
<bibRefCitation author="Titgen, R. H." pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refId="ref53402" refString="Titgen, R. H. (1982) The systematics and ecology of the Decapods of Dubai, and their zoogeographic relationships to the Persian Gulf and the Western Indian Ocean. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Texas A &amp; M University, 292 pp." type="book" year="1982">Titgen (1982)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from the Persian Gulf, Dubai. We examined his small specimen (CL/CB = 5.93/4.82), which looks slightly different in regard to a CL/CB ratio which is about 1.2, but in the present specimens from the 
<collectingCountry box="[151,230,1588,1612]" name="Iran" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Qeshm</collectingCountry>
I. the carapace is clearly wider than long with CL/CB ratio average of 1.35. However, differences in the carapace-ratio can more likely be dependent on growth. Furthermore, 
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, D. S." box="[981,1159,1623,1647]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="95 - 118" refId="ref48564" refString="Johnson, D. S. (1958) The Indo-West Pacific species of the genus Polyonyx (Crustacea, Decapoda, Porcellanidae), Annals of Zoology, AGRA, 2 (8), 95 - 118." type="journal article" year="1958">Johnson (1958)</bibRefCitation>
stated that some small specimens from eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[435,492,1660,1684]" name="India" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">India</collectingCountry>
and the western Pacific examined by him have a ventral spine on the merus of cheliped; this was also noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[519,649,1695,1719]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="355 - 386" refId="ref47651" refString="Haig, J. (1964) Papers from D' Th. Mortensen's Pacific expedition 1914 - 1916. 81. Porcellanid crabs from the Indo-West Pacific. part I. Videtwk. Meddr. durlsk ncrturh, Foren., 126, 355 - 386." type="journal article" year="1964">Haig (1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Haig, J." box="[661,721,1695,1719]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="49 - 65" refId="ref47698" refString="Haig, J. (1966) The Porcellanidae (Crustacea, Anomura) of the Iranian Gulf and Gulf of Oman. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening i Kobenhaven, 129, 49 - 65." type="journal article" year="1966">1966</bibRefCitation>
). But in the present specimen, as usual, no spine is seen on this part of cheliped.
</paragraph>
